          "type": "thinking",
          "provider": "anthropic",
          "thinking": "The user wants to verify their understanding of Zig switch semantics compared to Java's switch. Let me confirm by checking the Zig documentation.",
          "finalTime": 1776943551020,
          "signature": "<redacted>",
          "startTime": 1776943550049
        },
        {
          "text": "Your understanding is correct. Zig switches have no fallthrough — each case is independent. An empty block `{}` means \"do nothing and exit the switch.\" No `break` needed. This is the opposite of Java/C where fallthrough is default and `break` is required.\n\nIn your code, patterns like `.empty => {}` and `.level => {}` simply mean \"this case is valid, do nothing.\"",
          "type": "text",
          "finalTime": 1776943554175,
